ATTACHMENT A Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 Bluestone Farm Solar, LLC Reactive Power Compensation
BLUESTONE FARM SOLAR, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Bluestone Farm Solar, LLC ("Bluestone Solar") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Bluestone Solar generating facility ("Bluestone Solar Facility").
The Bluestone Solar Facility is a solar generating facility located in Chase City, Virginia. The Bluestone Solar Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Virginia Electric and Power Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Bluestone Solar's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Bluestone Solar Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Bluestone Solar's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Bluestone Solar shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $680,932.32 The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $56,744.36
